The paper discusses the use of deep generative neural networks for conditional generation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The specific application of generating images suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The use of latent constraints and value functions for conditioning the generation process suggests artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) as additional sub-categories. Finally, the mention of generating discrete sequences of musical notes suggests a possible connection to signal processing (cs.SD).
